HEADWORD: Bemuse
<hw>Be*muse"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To muddle, daze,
or partially stupefy, as with liquor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A parson much <qex>bemused</qex> in beer.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

